verbose_text: BAL findings of increased numbers of lymphocytes, eosinophils, fibroblasts, and dysplastic type II pneumocytes may aid in the diagnosis of chemotherapy induced lung injury; however, none of these findings are diagnostic.
evidence: BAL findings of increased numbers of lymphocytes, eosinophils, fibroblasts, and dysplastic type II pneumocytes may aid in the diagnosis of chemotherapy-induced lung injury
